results.question:
You may not obtain a learners license if...? 
(i) You already have a license that authorizes the driving of the same vehicle class, 
(ii) You are declared unfit to obtain a driving license for a certain period and that period still prevails, 
(iii) Your license was suspended temporarily and the suspension has not yet expired
incorrectAnswer: A. (i) only is correct
B. (ii) and (iii) only are correct
results.correctAnswer: C. (i); (ii) and (iii) are correct

results.question: Sign warns you that there is...
incorrectAnswer: A. Possibly pedestrians ahead.
C. Possibly school kids close to or in the road.
results.correctAnswer: B. A marked pedestrian crossing ahead.

results.question: When are you allowed to drive your vehicle on the right-hand side of a road with traffic in both directions?
incorrectAnswer: A. When you switch the emergency lights of your vehicle on.
C. Under no circumstances.
results.correctAnswer: B. When a traffic officer orders you to do so.

results.question: Sign shows you that you...
incorrectAnswer: A. Can expect a sharp bent to the right
B. Will get a one-way road to the right
results.correctAnswer: C. Must turn right at the next road.

results.question: You are not allowed to stop...
incorrectAnswer: A. Where you are also prohibited to park.
C. Opposite a vehicle, where the roadway is 10m wide.
results.correctAnswer: B. 5m from a bridge.

results.question: Sign shows you that...
incorrectAnswer: B. The freeway ends.
C. There is a narrow bridge ahead.
results.correctAnswer: A. The road narrows from both sides.

results.question: Road marking RTM 1 in the sketch  shows you  that you...
incorrectAnswer: B. If you are driving in A, must reduce speed and drive on if it is safe.
C. If you are driving in B, can pass A if there are no other vehicles in the intersection.
results.correctAnswer: A. If you are driving in A, must stop before this line and drive on when it is safe.

results.question: Warning sign shows you that...
incorrectAnswer: A. There is a possibility of  a flood ahead.
C. There is a low water bridge ahead.
results.correctAnswer: B. The road end because of water ahead.

results.question: At an intersection...
incorrectAnswer: B. Vehicles have the right of way over pedestrians.
C. You can use a stop sign as a yield sign if there is no other traffic.
results.correctAnswer: A. You must yield to oncoming traffic if you want to turn right.

results.question: Road marking shows you that...
incorrectAnswer: A. The road surface is uneven.
C. It is a lane reserved for buses only.
results.correctAnswer: B. Traffic may not overtake or cross it on either side.

results.question:
When you want to change lanes and drive from **LI to L2** in the sketch below you must. 
(i) only do it when it is safe to do so. 
(ii) switch your indicators on in time to show what you are going to do. 
(iii) use the mirror(s) of your vehicle to ensure that you know of other traffic.
incorrectAnswer: A. Only (i) and (ii) are correct
C. Only (ii) and (iii) are correct
results.correctAnswer: B. All of the above are correct.

results.question: Road marking **Z5** warns you that...
incorrectAnswer: B. Roads cross ahead.
C. The freeway ends ahead.
results.correctAnswer: A. There is a level crossing with one railway line ahead.

results.question:
If you see that someone wants to overtake you, you must...
(i)  keep to the left as far as is safe. 
(ii)  not drive faster. 
(iii)  give hand signals to allow the person to pass safely
incorrectAnswer: B. All of the above are correct
C. (ii) Only is correct
results.correctAnswer: A. (i) and (ii) only are correct

results.question: When you see sign **R2.1** you must...
incorrectAnswer: A. Know that that section of the road is for the use of pedestrians only.
C. Stop because school kids might cross the road.
results.correctAnswer: B. Give right of way to pedestrians who would like to cross the street

results.question: When you drive...
incorrectAnswer: A. You must have two hands on the steering wheel..
C. You must wear shoes with rubber soles.
results.correctAnswer: B. your vision of the road and the traffic must be unobstructed.

results.question: Sign warns you that the road...
incorrectAnswer: A. Has many curves.
C. Surface is damaged.
results.correctAnswer: B. Is slippery when it is wet.

results.question: The legal speed which you may drive...
incorrectAnswer: A. Is always 120 km/h outside towns/cities.
B. Can be determined by yourself if you look at the number of lanes that the road has.
results.correctAnswer: C. Is shown to you by signs next to the road.

results.question: Sign warns you that...
incorrectAnswer: A. There is a compulsory police stop ahead.
C. You are now entering an urban area
results.correctAnswer: B. There is a robot ahead.

results.question: Where may you legally stop with your vehicle?
incorrectAnswer: A. 4 m From a tunnel
B. 5 m From a pedestrian crossing
results.correctAnswer: C. 6 m From a railway crossing

results.question: What does warning sign shows you?
incorrectAnswer: A. The road winds ahead.
B. A number of sharp curves is ahead
results.correctAnswer: C. A concealed entrance to the left is followed by one to the right.

results.question: If you are driving towards the circle, and there are also vehicles from the other three sides, you...
incorrectAnswer: A. Must always wait for the vehicle from your right before you drive on.
C. Must stop with all the vehicles and only drive on when it is safe.
results.correctAnswer: B. May drive on if you were the first vehicle over the line.

results.question: Sign shows you that only ... may park there.
incorrectAnswer: B. Motorcars that load or unload
C. Construction vehicles
results.correctAnswer: A. Goods vehicles that load or unload

results.question:
You may not... 
(i) Run the engine of your vehicle unattended, 
(ii) Use your vehicle without a cap on the fuel tank, 
(iii) Spin the wheels of your vehicle when pulling off.
incorrectAnswer: A. (i) and (ii) only are correct
B. (ii) only is correct
results.correctAnswer: C. All of the above are correct

results.question: When the robot is red and the green arrow flashes to the right, it shows you that...
incorrectAnswer: A. Only pedestrians may walk.
C. All traffic must turn right there.
results.correctAnswer: B. If you want to turn right, you may go.

results.question: What is the maximum period of time that a vehicle may be parked in one  place on a road outside urban areas?
incorrectAnswer: A. 7 Days
B. 48 Hours
results.correctAnswer: C. 24 Hours

results.question: When you see sign you must...
incorrectAnswer: A. Look out for road works where tractors operate.
B. Know that only agricultural vehicles may drive there.
results.correctAnswer: C. Be on the lookout for agricultural vehicles that may be on the road.

results.question:
When may you not pass another vehicle? When you... 
(i) Are nearing the top of a hill. 
(ii) Are nearing a curve. 
(iii) Can only see 100 m in front of you because of smoke over the road.
incorrectAnswer: A. (i) Only is correct
C. (i) and (ii) Only are correct
results.correctAnswer: B. All of the above are correct.

results.question: Warning sign shows you that...
incorrectAnswer: B. Potholes are to be found on the road ahead.
C. The road is ending ahead
results.correctAnswer: A. The road on which you are driving is going to change to a gravel road.

results.question: If you come to a traffic light and the red light flashes, you must...
incorrectAnswer: A. Stop and wait for the light to change to green before you go..
C. Look out for a road block as the light shows you a police stop.
results.correctAnswer: B. Stop and only go if it is safe to do so.

results.question: What does sign shows you?
incorrectAnswer: B. If you cannot see more than 100m in front of you, switch your lights on.
C. Dangerous conditions for the next 100 km.
results.correctAnswer: A. You are not allowed to travel faster than 100 km/h at night.

results.question: The furthest that your vehicle's dim lights may shine in front of you, is ... M.
Road markings RTM3 in the sketch...
incorrectAnswer: A. Show you that you may not stop further than the front one of the two.
C. Are lines that indicate another traffic lane..
results.correctAnswer: B. Are the lines where pedestrians walk..

results.question: What is important with regard to the hooter of your vehicle?
incorrectAnswer: B. Someone must hear it from a distance of at least 45 m.
C. You may use it to get the attention of someone that you would like to offer a lift.
results.correctAnswer: A. The tone of pitch of the sound may not change.

results.question: Look in the sketch ,  When you see road marking (a), you …
incorrectAnswer: A. May not park there because it is parking for ambulances only.
C. Know it is a lane reserved for emergency vehicles.
results.correctAnswer: B. May not park there at all

results.question: You may...
incorrectAnswer: A. Drive your vehicle on the sidewalk,
C. Leave the engine of your vehicle running when you put petrol in it
results.correctAnswer: B. Allow your vehicle to move backwards only if it is safe to do so.

results.question: If you see sign,you know that...
incorrectAnswer: B. Vehicles with a mass of more than 10 tone may not drive there.
C. That section of the road can only carry vehicles that weigh up to 10 tone.
results.correctAnswer: A. Vehicles with a mass of 10 tone and less may not drive there.

results.question:
When do you have right of way? 
(i) When you are within a traffic circle.
(ii) When you have stopped first at a four-way stop. 
(iii) When you want to turn right at an intersection in a two-way road.
incorrectAnswer: B. All of the above are correct.
C. Only (i) is correct.
results.correctAnswer: A. Only (i) and (ii) are correct.

results.question: Arrow E in the sketch, shows you that you...
incorrectAnswer: B. Can turn right or move straight on if it is safe.
C. Can still change lanes if you want to go on straight.
results.correctAnswer: A. Must turn right from that lane.

results.question: The last action that you must take before moving to another lane is to...
incorrectAnswer: A. Switch on your indicator.
C. Look in the rear view mirror.
results.correctAnswer: B. Check the blind spot

results.question: Sign shows you that there is a...
incorrectAnswer: B. Obstruction left of the road.
C. Detour to the left
results.correctAnswer: A. Sharp curve to the left ahead

results.question:
You may overtake another vehicle on the left-hand side... 
(i) When that vehicle is going to turn right and the road is wide enough that it is not  necessary to drive on the shoulder. 
(ii) Where the road has two lanes for traffic in the same direction. 
(iii) If a police officer instructs you to do so.
incorrectAnswer: A. (iii) Only is correct.
B. (ii) and (iii) Only are correct
results.correctAnswer: C. All of the above a re correct

results.question: Road marking shows you that you must...
incorrectAnswer: A. Stop.
B. Look out for school kids.
results.correctAnswer: C. Yield to all users of the road and possibly also trains.

results.question: The license for your vehicle (clearance certificate) is valid for...
incorrectAnswer: B. 90 Days.
C. 21 Days.
results.correctAnswer: A. 12 Months.

results.question: Sign shows you that...
incorrectAnswer: B. You are not allowed to turn right there.
C. There is a T-junction to the right.
results.correctAnswer: A. The road turning to the right, ends ahead.

results.question:
Your vehicle's headlights must be switched on.... 
(i) At any time of the day when you cannot see persons and vehicles 150 m in front  of you. 
(ii) From sunset to sunrise. 
(iii) When it rains and you cannot see vehicles 100 m in front of you.
incorrectAnswer: A. (ii) Only is correct.
B. (i) and (ii) Only are correct.
results.correctAnswer: C. All of the above are correct.

results.question: Sign shows you that there is a...
incorrectAnswer: A. Curve to the left ahead.
C. Temporary detour to the left.
results.correctAnswer: B. Temporary obstruction left of the road.

results.question: At an intersection ...
incorrectAnswer: B. Vehicles have the right of way over pedestrians.
C. You can use a stop sign as a yield sign if there is no other traffic.
results.correctAnswer: A. You must yield to oncoming traffic if you want to turn right.

results.question: Sign shows you that you must...
incorrectAnswer: A. Turn left at the stop sign.
B. Stop and then turn left or drive straight on.
results.correctAnswer: C. Stop but if you want to turn left, you can use it as a yield sign.

results.question: The maximum distance between two vehicles which are being towed is  ...m
Sign forbids...
incorrectAnswer: B. All motor vehicles to drive past this sign.
C. Minibuses to pick up passengers.
results.correctAnswer: A. Minibuses to drive past this sign.

results.question:
The lights of your vehicle parked on a public road between sunset and sunrise need not lighted when the vehicle is parked... 
(i) 10m from a lighted street lamp. 
(ii) Next to the roadway of the road. 
(iii) In a demarcated parking area
incorrectAnswer: B. Only (i) and (iii) are correct.
C. Only (ii) and (iii) are correct.
results.correctAnswer: A. All of the above are correct.

results.question: Sign K3 shows you that you...
incorrectAnswer: B. May not park there for more than 3 hours.
C. Are only allowed to drive there between 06:00 and 09:00.
results.correctAnswer: A. May not drive there between 06:00 and 09:00.

results.question: It is illegal when you drive and a passenger...
incorrectAnswer: A. Sits directly behind you when you only have a learner's license.
B. Fiddles with the motor radio's volume knob.
results.correctAnswer: C. Rides on the bumper of your vehicle.

results.question: Sign G9 shows you that...
incorrectAnswer: A. You must use that part of the road.
C. There is parking for motor cars there.
results.correctAnswer: B. You can use that part of the road if you wish.

results.question: The tread pattern of you vehicle's tires may not be less than...mm
Sign shows you that...
incorrectAnswer: A. No taxis may drive there.
C. You may not park your motor car there.

To stop your vehicle, you must use number...
